The paper discusses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The focus is on comparing expected and distributional approaches to reinforcement learning, which are both related to optimization and decision making. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses control settings and approximators, which are related to control theory and systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper includes theoretical and empirical analyses, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
